---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import ProjectNav from "../components/ProjectNav.astro";
---

<Layout title="Results ‚Äî Paulina Castillo">
  <h1 class="mt-10 mb-6 text-center text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-zinc-50 tracking-tight leading-tight">
    The Beauty of Less: Optimization and Machine Learning in Network Design
  </h1>

  <ProjectNav active="results" />

<section class="relative overflow-hidden rounded-2xl
  bg-gradient-to-br from-zinc-800 via-zinc-900 to-black
  shadow-lg p-6 md:p-10 mt-8 border border-zinc-800/60">

  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-zinc-100 tracking-tight">
      The End of the Flow ‚Äî Where the Water Story Finds Its Balance
    </h2>

    <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-[1.05rem] text-zinc-300">
      It started with a late shower and a broken pipe. It became nodes, edges, and costs.
      And it ended in a real network: <span class="font-medium text-zinc-100">Shelby County, Tennessee</span>.
      Every day was a scenario, every pipe a decision, and the goal was simple: keep the water moving with intention.
    </p>

    <!-- Callout quote -->
    <div class="mt-6 rounded-2xl border border-zinc-700 bg-zinc-800/70 backdrop-blur px-5 py-4">
      <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <div class="shrink-0 text-2xl leading-none">üí°</div>
        <p class="text-zinc-200 leading-relaxed">
          ‚ÄúResilience isn‚Äôt about adding more ‚Äî it‚Äôs about keeping the right connections.
          Under structural limits, a system can preserve its function by reorganizing intelligently.‚Äù
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Visuals area -->
    <h3 class="mt-8 text-xl md:text-2xl font-semibold text-zinc-100 tracking-tight">
      Shelby County Water Network (applied with this framework)
    </h3>
    <p class="mt-2 text-zinc-300">
      Below you‚Äôll compare the <span class="text-zinc-100 font-medium">Original</span> layout and the
      <span class="text-zinc-100 font-medium">Reduced</span> design found by the optimization + RL pipeline.
    </p>

    <!-- Before/After cards (vac√≠as por ahora) -->
    <div class="mt-5 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-zinc-700 bg-zinc-900/50 p-4">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
          <span class="text-sm text-zinc-400">Layer</span>
          <span class="text-xs rounded-full border border-zinc-700 px-2 py-0.5 text-zinc-300">Original</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-3 aspect-video rounded-lg bg-zinc-800/60 grid place-content-center text-zinc-500 text-sm">
          <span>Original network placeholder</span>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-3 text-xs text-zinc-400">Full pipeline set; reference behavior.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-xl border border-zinc-700 bg-zinc-900/50 p-4">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
          <span class="text-sm text-zinc-400">Layer</span>
          <span class="text-xs rounded-full border border-zinc-700 px-2 py-0.5 text-zinc-300">Reduced</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-3 aspect-video rounded-lg bg-zinc-800/60 grid place-content-center text-zinc-500 text-sm">
          <span>Reduced network placeholder</span>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-3 text-xs text-zinc-400">Simplified topology preserving flow behavior.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Results: s√≥lo agua, contundente, dejando espacio para figuras -->
    <h3 class="mt-8 text-xl md:text-2xl font-semibold text-zinc-100 tracking-tight">
      Water ‚Äî What held up when pipes went missing
    </h3>
    <div class="mt-4 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-3">
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-zinc-700 bg-zinc-800/60 px-4 py-3 text-center">
        <div class="text-sm text-zinc-400">Structure kept</div>
        <div class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-100">‚âà 66%</div>
        <div class="text-xs text-zinc-500">of original arcs</div>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-zinc-700 bg-zinc-800/60 px-4 py-3 text-center">
        <div class="text-sm text-zinc-400">Flow efficiency</div>
        <div class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-100">‚âà 95‚Äì97%</div>
        <div class="text-xs text-zinc-500">under ¬±10% demand</div>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-zinc-700 bg-zinc-800/60 px-4 py-3 text-center">
        <div class="text-sm text-zinc-400">Compute</div>
        <div class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-100">~90% CPU</div>
        <div class="text-xs text-zinc-500">batched MCF + VPG</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Ideas para mostrar resultados (sin im√°genes) -->
    <div class="mt-5 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-3">
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-zinc-700 bg-zinc-900/50 p-4">
        <div class="text-sm text-zinc-400">Interactive idea</div>
        <div class="mt-1 text-zinc-100 font-medium">Before/After slider</div>
        <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-zinc-400">Drag to reveal reduced edges; fade removed arcs.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-zinc-700 bg-zinc-900/50 p-4">
        <div class="text-sm text-zinc-400">Flow behavior</div>
        <div class="mt-1 text-zinc-100 font-medium">Cost distribution match</div>
        <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-zinc-400">Overlay histograms (original vs. reduced) across scenarios.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-zinc-700 bg-zinc-900/50 p-4">
        <div class="text-sm text-zinc-400">Scenario view</div>
        <div class="mt-1 text-zinc-100 font-medium">Scatter x=y</div>
        <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-zinc-400">Each point is a day; closeness to the diagonal = fidelity.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Conclusi√≥n breve (sin hablar de gas/power en detalle, pero dej√°ndolas como ‚Äúotra historia‚Äù) -->
    <p class="mt-8 leading-relaxed text-[1.05rem] text-zinc-300">
      The water story ends here: fewer pipes, same purpose ‚Äî flow that stays where it needs to be.
      The same framework also ventured into <span class="text-zinc-100 font-medium">power</span> and
      <span class="text-zinc-100 font-medium">gas</span> networks with equally compelling patterns‚Ä¶ but that‚Äôs another story.
    </p>

    <!-- Nota sutil de tesis -->
    <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-zinc-500">
      <span class="opacity-90">Footnote:</span> this project formed the core of my <span class="text-zinc-300">Master‚Äôs thesis</span>.
      The lasting lesson? <em>Less can carry more ‚Äî if you keep the right connections.</em>
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Soft glows -->
  <div class="pointer-events-none absolute -right-16 -bottom-16 h-64 w-64 rounded-full bg-sky-500/10 blur-3xl"></div>
  <div class="pointer-events-none absolute -left-20 -top-20 h-72 w-72 rounded-full bg-emerald-500/10 blur-3xl"></div>
</section>


</Layout>
